BILLSCAN PHONE NEGOTIATION SCRIPT
Bill: {{facilityName}} | Total: ${{totalBilled}}

=== OPENING ===
"Hi, my name is [YOUR NAME] and I'm calling about a bill from {{facilityName}}.
My account number is [ACCOUNT NUMBER]. I've reviewed my bill and have some
questions about the charges."

=== KEY POINTS TO MAKE ===

1. REQUEST ITEMIZED BILL
"I'd like to request a complete itemized bill with CPT codes for every charge."

2. MENTION CMS RATES
"I've compared these charges to the 2026 CMS Medicare fee schedule and found
some significant discrepancies. My total was billed at ${{totalBilled}}, but
the CMS baseline is ${{totalCmsBaseline}} — a difference of ${{totalPotentialSavings}}."

3. CITE SPECIFIC OVERCHARGES
{{topFindings}}

4. ASK FOR SUPERVISOR IF NEEDED
"I'd like to speak with a patient advocate or billing supervisor about
negotiating these charges based on the CMS fee schedule."

5. ASK ABOUT FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE
"Do you have a financial assistance policy or charity care program?
As a patient, I have the right to apply."

=== WHAT TO DOCUMENT ===
- Date and time of call
- Name of representative
- Reference number
- Any commitments made

=== FOLLOW-UP ===
If unresolved, send a formal dispute letter and consider:
- State insurance commissioner complaint
- Hospital patient advocate
- Medical billing advocate (typically charges 25-35% of savings)
